; A comptime that USES a C-string but yields i64 — the tree-walk interpreter rejects
; the ECStr, while the compiled comptime engine (interp deletion step 1, mac-8) runs
; `(do c"hi" 0)` as real code and folds it to the literal 0, so this now BUILDS (exit 0).
(defn main [] (-> :i64) (comptime (do c"hi" 0)))
